It is the finding of the General Assembly that cultural opportunities and the arts have a direct and positive impact on the hotel industry through promotion of tourism and convention trade. The Kentucky Center for the Arts will serve as catalyst in the development of Louisville and Jefferson County as a major convention and entertainment center. The Kentucky Center for the Arts Corporation will have as management priority the stimulation of the Jefferson County hotel industry and promotion of tourism through:
The presentation of Kentucky and Louisville-area and nationally and internationally prominent arts activities which will attract regional audiences;
Regional and national promotion of events occurring within the Commonwealth, along with ancillary services and activities;
The development, in conjunction with local hotels and the arts and entertainment industry, of tourist packages including performance and group plans;
The active solicitation of arts related conferences and conventions;
The active participation with local hotels and convention bureaus in attracting non-arts related conferences and conventions, with the center serving as an important amenity;
The development of a Kentucky folklore program which will attract participants and an audience from throughout the state;
The contribution to cultural diversity and the attractiveness of Louisville and Jefferson County as a year-round tourist and entertainment attraction.
